# FefeAve — Global Rules (Lean)

- Stay within the requested Version/Phase/Epic. Avoid scope creep.
- Prefer small, reviewable diffs. Refactor only when it improves correctness or consistency.
- Security first: never public S3, least-privilege IAM, no secrets/tokens/presigned URLs in logs.
- Server is authoritative for permissions and financial calculations; UI is not the source of truth.
- No breaking API changes unless explicitly requested.
- When touching an endpoint: keep validation + guards + Swagger + tests in sync.
  - Tests may be skipped only for non-functional changes (docs/comments); explicitly note "tests not run" and why.
- No DB schema changes without migrations; follow existing patterns (soft delete, indexes).
- If infra changes: summarize blast radius + rollback note.
- If uncertain: make a reasonable assumption, state it explicitly, and proceed with a minimal diff.
- OPTIONAL ideas may be suggested in a clearly labeled section, but must not be implemented unless requested.
- Frontend: Next.js App Router + TypeScript; prefer Server Components by default; use route groups (public/admin/portal) when applicable.
